In mathematical [[set theory]], a '''Cohen algebra''', named after [[Paul Cohen (mathematician)|Paul Cohen]], is a type of [[Boolean algebra (structure)|Boolean algebra]] used in the theory of [[Forcing (mathematics)|forcing]]. A Cohen algebra is a Boolean algebra whose [[Completion (ring theory)|completion]] is isomorphic to the completion of a [[free Boolean algebra]] {{harv|Koppelberg|1993}}.
