'''HashClash''' was a [[distributed computing]] project to find [[hash collision|collision]]s in the [[MD5]] [[hash algorithm]]. It was based at Department of [[Mathematics]] and [[Computer Science]] at the [[Eindhoven University of Technology]], and [[Marc Stevens (cryptology)|Marc Stevens]] initiated the project as part of his [[master's degree]] [[thesis]].

The project ended after Stevens defended his M.Sc. thesis in June 2007.<ref>Stevens's thesis "On Collisions for MD5" is [http://www.win.tue.nl/hashclash/On%20Collisions%20for%20MD5%20-%20M.M.J.%20Stevens.pdf available for download].</ref>

